HEADWORD: Incogitant
<hw>In*cog"i*tant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>incogitans</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>cogitans</ets>,
p. pr. of <ets>cogitare</ets> to think. See <er>Cogitate</er>.]</ety>
<def>Thoughtless; inconsiderate.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Men are careless and <qex>incogitant</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Goodman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incogitantly</ent>⟦br⟧
